{"actual_usd":0.12523499999999999,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":249,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24300,"reply":"\"The resurrection wasn't a dress rehearsal.\" *I rub a thumb along a dried seam of clay on my apron, watching a strip of morning light creep across the floorboards.* \"It was the breach in the wall—the actual thing. But a breach isn't the same as the whole city being remade by noon.\"\n\n*I lean back a little, feeling the bench complain under me.* \"I think we're living in the strange middle of it. Christ is risen, so death's been dealt its true wound already... but the kingdom's still arriving the way dawn arrives over a town—first the rim of light, then windows catching, then finally the whole street plain to everybody. Not fizzled. Begun.\"\n\n\"The hard part, maybe, is that we'd like victory to feel immediate and total.\" *I glance toward the window, where the sky's gone bright behind a passing cloud.* \"But a lot of God's work seems to come seed first, harvest later. The resurrection is seed and guarantee and opening of the age to come—all of that at once. We just haven't reached the day when every last thing is brought under it.\"\n\n\"What part of that is catching in your throat—the waiting, or the way it seems hidden?\"","rolling_24h_usd":71.64023999999998,"run_id":"4817baf1-52ab-4f73-805e-99f992fc4ef9"}
